productivity_vs_labor_costs.description: P2 — When productivity rises but ULC stays high, firms are squeezing more output from fewer workers. Widening gap = AI substitution accelerating.
productivity_vs_labor_costs.interpretation: Leader series leads follower by 1 periods with correlation 0.5853. Moderate positive relationship.

profits_vs_wages.description: P3 — Profits rising while wage growth flat = successful cost substitution. Divergence confirms AI is enabling margin expansion.
profits_vs_wages.interpretation: Leader series leads follower by 1 periods with correlation -0.3471. Weak negative relationship.

beveridge_curve.description: P5 — Beveridge curve shift: if openings fall while unemployment rises, the matching function has broken. Skills mismatch + AI substitution.
beveridge_curve.interpretation: Leader series leads follower by 0 periods with correlation -0.6576. Moderate negative relationship.

creative_destruction.description: P2+P4 — Rising delinquency + rising new business formation = creative destruction in action. Old firms dying, new ones forming.
creative_destruction.interpretation: Leader series leads follower by 0 periods with correlation 0.2366. Weak positive relationship.

stress_propagation.description: Capital stress — VIX leads HY spread: equity fear precedes credit stress. Time between them = warning window.
stress_propagation.interpretation: Leader series leads follower by 5 periods with correlation -0.1592. Weak negative relationship.
